Reasoning: The paper discusses the integration of neural networks into safety-critical systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The use of reinforcement learning in a simulated robot manipulation task suggests that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on measuring the dependability of neural networks and designing a safety function suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of metrics to evaluate the performance of the neural network suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
